    "Let us introduce the marginal distributiong(t, A) = ∫ I f (t, A, w)dw,and consider the Fokker-Planck equation (13) with only the operator Q p (f, f).",
    "Let us also assume that the initial level of activity inside the population is bounded, i.e.",
    "the initial distribution f in (A, w) = f (0, A, w) has a compact support.",
    "For any value of the constant a p from cases (i), (ii) or (iii), since the activity level varies according to the drift term of (14) acting on A alone, one expects that the support of the distribution remains compact for any t > 0.",
    "We make this argument rigorous in the following proposition."
  ]
}